question:
{"text": "Based on the VSEPR model, match the xenon compounds given in List-I with the corresponding geometries and the number of lone pairs on xenon given in List-II and choose the correct option.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) XeF}_2 & (1) \text{ Trigonal bipyramidal and two lone pair of electrons} \\ \hline \text{(Q) XeF}_4 & (2) \text{ Tetrahedral and one lone pair of electrons} \\ \hline \text{(R) XeO}_3 & (3) \text{ Octahedral and two lone pair of electrons} \\ \hline \text{(S) XeO}_3\text{F}_2 & (4) \text{ Trigonal bipyramidal and no lone pair of electrons} \\ \hline & (5) \text{ Trigonal bipyramidal and three lone pair of electrons} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}

{"text": "Let the function $f:[1,\infty)\rightarrow \mathbb{R}$ be defined by
$$f(t)=\left\{\begin{array}{ll}
(-1)^{n+1}2 & ; \quad \text{if } t=2n-1, n\in\mathbb{N} \\
\frac{(2n+1-t)}{2}f(2n-1)+\frac{(t-(2n-1))}{2}f(2n+1) & ; \quad \text{if } 2n-1<t<2n+1, n\in\mathbb{N}
\end{array}\right.$$
Define $g(x)=\int\limits_{1}^{x}f(t)dt, x\in(1,\infty)$. Let $ \alpha $ denote the number of solutions of the equation $g(x)=0 $ in the interval (1, 8] and $ \beta=\lim\limits_{x\rightarrow 1^{+}}\frac{g(x)}{x-1} $ . Then the value of $ \alpha+\beta $ is equal to ____.", "image_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/1H_ya_NoHYvzq9pv5B4PH8LBrcMkUoafA=w1200"}

{"text": "Let $\gamma \in \mathbb{R}$ be such that the lines $L_{1}:\frac{x+11}{1}=\frac{y+21}{2}=\frac{z+29}{3}$ and $L_{2}:\frac{x+16}{3}=\frac{y+11}{2}=\frac{z+4}{\gamma}$ intersect. Let $R_{1}$ be the point of intersection of $L_{1}$ and $L_{2}$. Let $O = (0,0,0)$, and $\hat{n}$ denote a unit normal vector to the plane containing both the lines $L_{1}$ and $L_{2}$. Match each entry in List-I to the correct entry in List-II.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) } \gamma \text{ equals} & (1) \text{ } -\hat{i} - \hat{j} + \hat{k} \\ \text{(Q) A possible choice for } \hat{n} \text{ is} & (2) \text{ } \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}} \\ \text{(R) } \overrightarrow{OR_1} \text{ equals} & (3) \text{ } 1 \\ \text{(S) A possible value of } |\overrightarrow{OR_1} \cdot \hat{n}| \text{ is} & (4) \text{ } \frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}\hat{i} - \frac{2}{\sqrt{6}}\hat{j} + \frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}\hat{k} \\ & (5) \text{ } \sqrt{\frac{2}{3}} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}

{"text": "Consider the following volume – temperature (V – T) diagram for the expansion of 5 moles of an ideal monoatomic gas.

Consider only $P – V$ work is involved, the total change in enthalpy (in Joule) for the transformation of state in the sequence $X \rightarrow Y \rightarrow Z$ is ____.

[Use the given data: Molar heat capacity of the gas for the given temperature range, $C_{v,m} = 12 \text{ J K}^{-1} \text{ mol}^{-1}$ and gas constant, $R = 8.3 \text{ J K}^{-1} \text{ mol}^{-1}$]", "image_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/1naZulytfuzGl9CbaJ1vitGnJf3_nYPP3=w1200"}

{"text": "Let N denote the set of all natural numbers, and Z denote the set of all integers. Consider the functions $f$: $N \rightarrow Z$ and $g$: $Z \rightarrow N$ defined by
$$
f(n) = \begin{cases} \frac{(n+1)}{2} \text{ if } n \text{ is odd}, \\ \frac{(4-n)}{2} \text{ if } n \text{ is even}, \end{cases}
$$
and
$$
g(n) = \begin{cases} 3+2n \text{ if } n \geq 0, \\ -2n \text{ if } n < 0. \end{cases}
$$
Define $(g \circ f)$", "image_url": null}

{"text": "Consider the following frequency distribution:

$$\begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|} \hline \text{Value} & 4 & 5 & 8 & 9 & 6 & 12 & 11 \\ \hline \text{Frequency} & 5 & f_1 & f_2 & 2 & 1 & 1 & 3 \\ \hline \end{array}$$

Suppose that the sum of the frequencies is 19 and the median of this frequency distribution is 6. Match each entry in List-I to the correct entry in List-II and choose the correct option.", "image_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/1pERi07rWzIgqY8eMGzuN-pR59IjuO0zh=w1180"}

{"text": "Let $\vec{w} = \hat{i} + \hat{j} - 2\hat{k}$, and $\vec{u}$ and $\vec{v}$ be two vectors, such that $\vec{u} \times \vec{v} = \vec{w}$ and $\vec{v} \times \vec{w} = \vec{u}$. Let $\alpha, \beta, \gamma$ and $t$ be real numbers such that $\vec{u} = \alpha \hat{i} + \beta \hat{j} + \gamma \hat{k}$, $-t\alpha + \beta + \gamma = 0$, $\alpha - t\beta + \gamma = 0$, and $\alpha + \beta - t\gamma = 0$. Match each entry in List-I to the correct entry in List-II.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) } |\vec{v}|^2 \text{ is equal to} & (1) \text{ 0} \\ \hline \text{(Q) If } \alpha = \sqrt{3}, \text{ then } \gamma^2 \text{ is equal to} & (2) \text{ 1} \\ \hline \text{(R) If } \alpha = \sqrt{3}, \text{ then } (\beta + \gamma)^2 \text{ is equal to} & (3) \text{ 2} \\ \hline \text{(S) If } \alpha = \sqrt{2}, \text{ then } t + 3 \text{ is equal to} & (4) \text{ 3} \\ \hline & (5) \text{ 5} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}

{"text": "List-I shows various functional dependencies of energy ($E$) on the atomic number ($Z$). Energies associated with certain phenomena are given in List-II. Choose the option that describes the correct match between the entries in List-I to those in List-II.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) } E \propto Z^2 & (1) \text{ energy of characteristic x-rays} \\ \hline \text{(Q) } E \propto (Z-1)^2 & (2) \text{ electrostatic part of the nuclear binding energy for stable nuclei with mass numbers in the range 30 to 170} \\ \hline \text{(R) } E \propto Z(Z-1) & (3) \text{ energy of continuous x-rays} \\ \hline \text{(S) } E \text{ is practically independent of } Z & (4) \text{ average nuclear binding energy per nucleon for stable nuclei with mass number in the range 30 to 170} \\ \hline & (5) \text{ energy of radiation due to electronic transitions from hydrogen-like atoms} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}

{"text": "The correct match of the group reagents in List-I for precipitating the metal ion given in List-II from solutions, is

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) Passing H}_2\text{S in the presence of NH}_4\text{OH} & (1) \text{ Cu}^{2+} \\ \hline \text{(Q) (NH}_4)_2\text{CO}_3 \text{ in the presence of NH}_4\text{OH} & (2) \text{ Al}^{3+} \\ \hline \text{(R) NH}_4\text{OH in the presence of NH}_4\text{Cl} & (3) \text{ Mn}^{2+} \\ \hline \text{(S) Passing H}_2\text{S in the presence of dilute HCl} & (4) \text{ Ba}^{2+} \\ \hline & (5) \text{ Mg}^{2+} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}

{"text": "The major products obtained from the reactions in List-II are the reactants for the named reactions mentioned in List-I. Match each entry in List-I with the appropriate entry in List-II and choose the correct option.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) Stephen reaction} & \text{(1) Toluene } \xrightarrow[\text{(ii) H}_3\text{O}^+]{\text{(i) CrO}_2\text{Cl}_2/\text{CS}_2} \\ \hline \text{(Q) Sandmeyer reaction} & \text{(2) Benzoic acid } \xrightarrow[\text{(iii) P}_4\text{O}_{10}, \Delta]{\text{(i) PCl}_5, \text{ (ii) NH}_3} \\ \hline \text{(R) Hoffmann bromamide degradation reaction} & \text{(3) Nitrobenzene } \xrightarrow[\text{(ii) HCl, NaNO}_2 (273-278 \text{ K}), \text{ H}_2\text{O}]{\text{(i) Fe, HCl}} \\ \hline \text{(S) Cannizzaro reaction} & \text{(4) Toluene } \xrightarrow[\text{(iii) SO}_2\text{Cl}_2, \text{ (iv) NH}_3]{\text{(i) Cl}_2/h\nu, \text{ H}_2\text{O, (ii) Tollen's reagent}} \\ \hline & \text{(5) Aniline } \xrightarrow[\text{(iii) aq. NaOH}]{\text{(i) (CH}_3\text{CO)}_2\text{O, Pyridine, (ii) HNO}_3, \text{ H}_2\text{SO}_4, 288 \text{ K}} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}

{"text": "Let the straight line $y=2x$ touch a circle with centre $(0, \alpha)$, $\alpha > 0$, and radius $r$ at a point $A_{1}$. Let $B_{1}$ be the point on the circle such that the line segment $A_{1}B_{1}$ is a diameter of the circle. Let $\alpha + r = 5 + \sqrt{5}$. Match each entry in List-I to the correct entry in List-II.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) } \alpha \text{ equals} & (1) \text{ } (-2, 4) \\ \text{(Q) } r \text{ equals} & (2) \text{ } \sqrt{5} \\ \text{(R) } A_{1} \text{ equals} & (3) \text{ } (-2, 6) \\ \text{(S) } B_{1} \text{ equals} & (4) \text{ } 5 \\ & (5) \text{ } (2, 4) \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}

{"text": "One mole of a monatomic ideal gas undergoes the cyclic process $J \rightarrow K \rightarrow L \rightarrow M \rightarrow J$, as shown in the P-T diagram. Match the quantities mentioned in List-I with their values in List-II and choose the correct option.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) Work done in the complete cyclic process} & (1) \text{ } RT_0 - 4RT_0 \ln 2 \\ \hline \text{(Q) Change in the internal energy of the gas in the process JK} & (2) \text{ } 0 \\ \hline \text{(R) Heat given to the gas in the process KL} & (3) \text{ } 3RT_0 \\ \hline \text{(S) Change in the internal energy of the gas in the process MJ} & (4) \text{ } -2RT_0 \ln 2 \\ \hline & (5) \text{ } -3RT_0 \ln 2 \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/1wWIHFSltTIGQKrFhBtuHmgnEd7ODU-uV=w1200"}

{"text": "The circuit shown in the figure contains an inductor $L = 25\text{ mH}$, a capacitor $C_0 = 10\mu F$, a resistor $R_0 = 5 \Omega$ and an ideal battery of $20\text{ V}$. The circuit also contains two keys $K_1$ and $K_2$. Initially, both the keys are open and there is no charge on the capacitor. At an instant, key $K_1$ is closed and immediately after this the current in $R_0$ is found to be $I_1$. After a long time, the current attains a steady state value $I_2$. Thereafter, $K_2$ is closed and simultaneously $K_1$ is opened and the voltage across $C_0$ oscillates with amplitude $V_0$ and angular frequency $\omega_0$. Match the quantities in List-I with List-II.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) The value of } I_1 \text{ in Ampere is} & (1) \text{ 0} \\ \hline \text{(Q) The value of } I_2 \text{ in Ampere is} & (2) \text{ 2} \\ \hline \text{(R) The value of } \omega_0 \text{ in kilo-radians/s is} & (3) \text{ 4} \\ \hline \text{(S) The value of } V_0 \text{ in Volt is} & (4) \text{ 20} \\ \hline & (5) \text{ 200} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/1vGVTaafStI_YUikHMSyciJsc76VsnmWM=w1200"}

{"text": "In the following reaction sequence, major product P is formed.

Glycerol reacts completely with excess P in the presence of an acid catalyst to form Q. Reaction of Q with excess NaOH followed by the treatment with CaCl$_2$ yields Ca – soap R, quantitatively. Starting with one mole of Q, the amount of R produced in gram is _____.

[Given, atomic weight: $H = 1$, $C = 12$, $N = 14$, $O = 16$, $Na = 23$, $Cl = 35$, $Ca = 40$]", "image_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/1nZGIcFqD44c23vLJc1HQJM_Zma3hbBzg=w1200"}

{"text": "Four identical thin, square metal sheets, $S_{1}$, $S_{2}$, $S_{3}$ and $S_{4}$, each of side $a$ are kept parallel to each other with equal distance $d$ ($d \ll a$) between them, as shown in the figure. Let $C_{0}=\varepsilon_{0} a^{2}/d$, where $\varepsilon_{0}$ is the permittivity of free space. Match the quantities mentioned in List-I with their values in List-II.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) The capacitance between } S_1 \text{ and } S_4, \text{ with } S_2 \text{ and } S_3 \text{ not connected, is} & (1) \text{ } 3C_0 \\ \hline \text{(Q) The capacitance between } S_1 \text{ and } S_4, \text{ with } S_2 \text{ shorted to } S_3, \text{ is} & (2) \text{ } C_0/2 \\ \hline \text{(R) The capacitance between } S_1 \text{ and } S_3, \text{ with } S_2 \text{ shorted to } S_4, \text{ is} & (3) \text{ } C_0/3 \\ \hline \text{(S) The capacitance between } S_1 \text{ and } S_2, \text{ with } S_3 \text{ shorted to } S_1, \text{ and } S_2 \text{ shorted to } S_4, \text{ is} & (4) \text{ } 2C_0/3 \\ \hline & (5) \text{ } 2C_0 \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/d/10hisnOGrJIc1e_yxb-Xbt29nbRPfTgXR=w1200"}

{"text": "A light ray is incident on the surface of a sphere of refractive index $n$ at an angle of incidence $\theta_{0}$. The ray partially refracts into the sphere with angle of refraction $\phi_{0}$ and then partly reflects from the back surface. The reflected ray then emerges out of the sphere after a partial refraction. The total angle of deviation of the emergent ray with respect to the incident ray is $\alpha$. Match the quantities mentioned in List-I with their values in List-II and choose the correct option.

$$\begin{array}{|l|l|} \hline \pmb{\text{List-I}} & \pmb{\text{List-II}} \\ \hline \text{(P) If } n = 2 \text{ and } \alpha = 180^{\circ}, \text{ then all possible values of } \theta_{0} \text{ will be} & (1) \text{ } 30^{\circ} \text{ and } 0^{\circ} \\ \hline \text{(Q) If } n = \sqrt{3} \text{ and } \alpha = 180^{\circ}, \text{ then all possible values of } \theta_{0} \text{ will be} & (2) \text{ } 60^{\circ} \text{ and } 0^{\circ} \\ \hline \text{(R) If } n = \sqrt{3} \text{ and } \alpha = 180^{\circ}, \text{ then all possible values of } \phi_{0} \text{ will be} & (3) \text{ } 45^{\circ} \text{ and } 0^{\circ} \\ \hline \text{(S) If } n = \sqrt{2} \text{ and } \theta_{0} = 45^{\circ}, \text{ then all possible values of } \alpha \text{ will be} & (4) \text{ } 150^{\circ} \\ \hline & (5) \text{ } 0^{\circ} \\ \hline \end{array}$$
", "image_url": null}
